Paint enviado como mock up para MT165

-reference image:1/ brought down the highlights on the tailfin of the fg to make it not look quite so reflective. Replace the existing tale with the element in this reference image mt165.dm.ref.exr 2/ made the legs supporting the water tower easier read.3/ added same red paint to prop cowling.4/ brighter highlights on the midground plane added subtle reflection to cockpit. Add slight sky reflection on front of plane.5/ refined shape and value of tents in midground 6/ added some more dark line detail into the PSP to make some of the pieces slightly irregular looking. Break up edge of PSP with mud and grass.7/ adjust perspective of tent. Make sure tents are seen thru the windscreens of the trucks in front of them.Adjust the value of the hills behind the tents to make them feels a little bit closer in regards to atmospheric perspective (slightly darker).Do this so there is not so much separation between the trees and the mountains. Craig feels the trees are a little bit cut out.8/Desaturate the grass and add a little bit of mud like in the foreground plate to help break it up.
